1
00:00:00,466 --> 00:00:01,700
welcome back everyone

2
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:05,400
today we are going to play twist space, a GTNH add-on

3
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:09,066
this quick video will focus mostly on the (?) details of the (exact?) mod

4
00:00:09,266 --> 00:00:10,400
and without further ado

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,533
our first highlight is an alternative version for a multi block steam forge hammer

6
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,300
but even before we look into it

7
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,666
the spotlight is quickly taken by the large steam alloy smelter

8
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:22,700
this expensive machine can do up to 48 parallels

9
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:26,333
requiring 1 amp of HV power to not void all of our (bronze?)

10
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:30,466
all that power is being generated by our new multi block solar boiler

11
00:00:30,466 --> 00:00:32,333
which we'll see better later on

12
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:37,833
moving on we can use some expensive but efficient basic steam generators to power our EBFs

13
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:40,933
while this new generator can reach over unit energy efficiency

14
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:43,700
it doesn't turn itself off when the load is removed

15
00:00:43,866 --> 00:00:46,100
and also can only produce LV power

16
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:50,400
so in MV we had to go back to steam turbines to overvolt our EBF

17
00:00:50,566 --> 00:00:53,700
next after we centralized power and did one more EBF upgrade

18
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:57,866
we set up some automation to properly craft enough circuits for our next highlight

19
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,600
the eye of wood

20
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:03,666
this machine will produce many random resources in exchange of a lot of lava

21
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:07,066
however, due to how limited the options for sourcing lava are

22
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:10,000
even the machine itself is wondering if that trade is worth it

23
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,533
moving to an even more questionable machine

24
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:15,200
I shall present you the Mega Brick Blast Furnace

25
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:19,633
this machine will require you to fuel it coal to produce steel at whatever speed you can feed it

26
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:23,100
until it decides to live up to its name and breaking itself

27
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,433
back to actual progress

28
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:26,233
we moved on from using solar boilers

29
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:29,033
to some high efficiency natural gas generators

30
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:32,266
those will keep up our new small AE2 system

31
00:01:32,266 --> 00:01:34,800
while we move on to the personal dimension

32
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,333
here we will meet two old friends we lost a long time ago

33
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:41,000
the processing factory and the processing array

34
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,600
and thanks to a twist space

35
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,500
we can also use dual input buses to ease automation

36
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:48,633
next we proceeded into building the usual infrastructure

37
00:01:48,633 --> 00:01:51,400
which at this time will be powered by the lightning spire

38
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,733
unlike lightening rods

39
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:55,933
this bigger version doesn't require a thunderstorm to generate energy

40
00:01:56,233 --> 00:01:58,866
it will however require a little bit of cruotheum to cool down

41
00:01:58,866 --> 00:02:01,033
and some iron for the periodic repairs

42
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,233
next we made a mega distillation tower

43
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:07,666
where we on demand every sort of distillation from platline to oil processing

44
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,700
this was also made easier thanks to the advanced Mega Oil Cracker

45
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:14,000
which removes the stricts requirements for input placements

46
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:17,066
then we built a maximum size advanced clean room

47
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,466
and if you thought this is big and white enough to make you go crazy

48
00:02:20,466 --> 00:02:23,333
well you didn't think yet of the cost of those filters

49
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,900
unlike a normal clean room

50
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:28,400
this one has no maintenance and no energy cost

51
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:32,333
next to keep up with our everything main net on demand run

52
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,833
we built a mega chemical reactor

53
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:36,466
before we even finish our first fusion reactor

54
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,433
once we reach fusion

55
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,266
we built an advanced circuit assembly line

56
00:02:40,266 --> 00:02:42,133
which has no input order requirement

57
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,866
and can hold multiple imprints

58
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,000
and if you thought this was overpowered

59
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
well the next machine is mind blowing

60
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:51,100
I shall present you the nether interface

61
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,933
just look at the output and the NEI crafting recipe

62
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,700
moving on we did a little bit of magic

63
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:59,100
just enough to get a laser meter miner

64
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:03,733
this multi block will quickly dig meters one row at a time with a bonus fortune of three

65
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,833
next to increase our magic automation speed

66
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,800
we build an industrial magic matrix

67
00:03:08,866 --> 00:03:13,066
which can use over aura nodes and laser tier energy to speed up magic infusions

68
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,433
thanks to this machine

69
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:17,066
we can now make dozens of infusions per second

70
00:03:17,266 --> 00:03:21,100
we also traded the risk of flux production with the risk of power fail

71
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:24,266
and if that machine was going to make you scream bloody hell

72
00:03:24,266 --> 00:03:26,066
well keep that for our next machine

73
00:03:26,066 --> 00:03:28,066
which is literally called bloody hell

74
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:30,633
as the name and all of that blood suggests

75
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:33,533
this machine will process blood magic altar recipes

76
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,700
and unlike the previous one

77
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,866
it doesn't even require energy to work

78
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:42,600
while I think those two are probably the best looking multi-blocks I ever seen in modded Minecraft

79
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,700
those are not the only good looking multi-block added by twist space

80
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:49,133
we also have stuff like the eco-sphere growth simulator

81
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:52,033
capable of making hundreds of thousands of logs per second

82
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:54,266
while using a single amp of UV energy

83
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,666
next to it we have the large industrial Cooking Factory

84
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:00,600
which can do coke oven recipes with maximum parallel

85
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:04,166
but that's not the only machine capable of doing integer 32 parallel

86
00:04:04,166 --> 00:04:05,833
we also have a sifter

87
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:06,266
a mixer

88
00:04:06,266 --> 00:04:07,200
a fluid heater

89
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,166
and a fluid extractor

90
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:11,033
that doubles as fluid solidifier capable of doing that

91
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:14,233
and if you thought Integer 32 parallel was too overpowered

92
00:04:14,233 --> 00:04:17,300
well we also have machines capable of doing perfect overclock

93
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,433
like the electrolyzer

94
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,300
that also doubles as a centrifuge

95
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:23,433
finally, to conclude this series of overpower multi blocks

96
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:27,833
we also have a machine that does chemical reactor recipes for 1/10 of the energy cost

97
00:04:28,066 --> 00:04:28,833
and on top of that

98
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:33,600
it also has some custom recipes that allow you to skip most of the chemical line processing steps

99
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,933
moving to some more complicated multi-block

100
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:40,433
we have this (valuable?) forge which uses pyrotheum to increase its heat capacity

101
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:42,600
while doing so, it also gains some energy discount

102
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,300
making neutronium super cheap

103
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:46,533
and of course to cool down all of those hot ingots

104
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:48,500
we also have a heat devourer machine

105
00:04:48,866 --> 00:04:50,400
we also have a laser powered laser

106
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,733
that someday will achieve perfect overclock

107
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,533
and a 4 in 1 metal working machine

108
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,733
that at some point will accept laser energy

109
00:04:57,033 --> 00:05:00,100
and of course 4 in 1 means we have to build four of those

110
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:04,700
we also have a wire mill that will grow its parallel count by becoming longer

111
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:09,100
and the last UV multi block we built is a (?) and vacuum furnace

112
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:12,833
and this one also will increase its parallel by becoming taller

113
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:15,466
next we made some microbacteria vats

114
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,733
those can make some quite big batches

115
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:22,833
which require some fine tweaking of the amount of fluid held in the output hatch to reach optimal efficiency

116
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:26,933
and with that, we can now afford the Mega Cutting Machine and the Mega Polarizer

117
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:28,333
in their smaller form

118
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:32,600
and yes those two can grow in size to achieve more parallelizer speed

119
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:35,233
next after building a mega assembly line

120
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,000
which doesn't require input separation

121
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,700
and can do 128 parallel

122
00:05:38,866 --> 00:05:40,233
we go back to our laser

123
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:42,333
which can make the cheapest DTPF fuel ever

124
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,933
by stacking the speed bonus from each of the casing upgrades

125
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:49,266
the other issue you normally have with DTPFs is the raw Infinity Catalyst

126
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:52,866
as usual, twist offers a new multi block to help with that

127
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,866
the general ore processing TST

128
00:05:54,866 --> 00:05:57,866
which multiplies the output of pure raw ores by four

129
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:01,500
it also gives a crazy amount of gems from gem ores

130
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,733
and on top of that it can also do infinite parallels

131
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:07,066
keeping up with our new starcore miner

132
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:09,633
capable of producing a crazy amount of minerals

133
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,833
to keep up with the new power requirement

134
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:14,066
we started working on an actual dyson sphere

135
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:18,333
to do so, we used the dyson launcher structure to send solar sails into space

136
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,633
and once we have some orbiting our star

137
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:24,200
we can start collecting that energy through our dyson (Earth cyber?) dish

138
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,533
and it was then that we realized that

139
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:29,466
this is not going to produce any meaningful amount of energy

140
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:34,033
we could improve our output by building our dyson sphere around a better star

141
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:36,400
but the output would only be 10 times more

142
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,033
which is still thousands of times less than what will be meaningful to us

143
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:46,133
at the same time, making enough solar sails with proper module management is probably expensive for the moment

144
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:49,233
so instead of turning those solar rays into energy

145
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,733
we started turning those into critical photons

146
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,266
which you can use to craft a bunch of machines

147
00:06:54,266 --> 00:06:56,466
or for a better energy source, antimatter

148
00:06:57,666 --> 00:07:00,533
after our failed attempt at a new way of gathering energy

149
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,733
we went back to our trusty naquadah fuel

150
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:08,733
and here we can easily merge all of the laser dynamo of our generator using laser smart nodes

151
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:12,933
next we use the super cheap battery recipes to clearly craft our gorge

152
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,400
which for the moment isn't much useful

153
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,600
since the mega volcano is about 1000 times more energy efficient

154
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:22,833
and the entropy destroyer has no problem cooling down an endless amount of hot ingots

155
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:28,233
the other usage of gorge won't be able to show off for a while is its plasma making capacity

156
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:32,400
this time we can quickly put an end to the growth of our fusion tunnel

157
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,066
with the tier 3 ball lightning

158
00:07:34,066 --> 00:07:37,000
capable of making crazy amount of plasma for super cheap

159
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:39,800
and that combined with the other twist multi blocks

160
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,333
will make producing the DTPF fuel basically free

161
00:07:42,866 --> 00:07:44,500
to put all of that stuff to good use

162
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,133
we needed a miracle on top of our assembly lines

163
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:51,800
the miracle top will perfectly overclock the crafting of any circuit or circuit part

164
00:07:51,866 --> 00:07:56,500
overwhelming, even a machine whose only purpose was to prevent power failing circuit conversion

165
00:07:57,066 --> 00:08:00,600
anyways with this, we can now start our eye of harmony progression

166
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,500
which we can speed up thanks to three new machines

167
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,900
the first one is the Astral Computing Array

168
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,833
which will greatly speed up our search

169
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,033
thanks to its huge liquid cooler rack

170
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:12,833
next we have the twisted Large Disassembler

171
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:16,400
which can uncraft anything that was made in an assembler or assembly line

172
00:08:16,433 --> 00:08:21,200
helping us recover some of the valuable materials contained inside our older eye of harmony casing

173
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,200
finally to power all of this

174
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,866
we started building a dyson sphere around a bigger star

175
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:28,633
endlessly shooting more and more mirrors around it

176
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:32,100
this dyson sphere setup has no upkeep costs

177
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,233
but by sending more mirrors

178
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:35,700
we can increase our energy production super linearly

179
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:39,800
however there is a limit at how much energy each our reciving station can collect

180
00:08:39,866 --> 00:08:41,633
so we had to build a few more of those

181
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:44,300
this will give our eye of harmony progression a huge push

182
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:47,500
but it will still leave us with enough time to work on new multi-block

183
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,666
such as the matter manipulator Genesis

184
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:52,066
which can either produce concentrated UU matter

185
00:08:52,066 --> 00:08:54,133
or huge amounts of normal UU matter

186
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:55,900
next we have the Miracle door

187
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,733
which will do alloy blast smelt recipes to ingot with infinite parallel

188
00:08:59,866 --> 00:09:02,066
then we made a micro space time fabricator

189
00:09:02,066 --> 00:09:04,900
which makes a couple of new parts and cheaper tesseracts

190
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,700
finally we have the super water purifier

191
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,833
which will make our water line redundant

192
00:09:10,266 --> 00:09:12,333
and after a few more upgrades and some waiting time

193
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:15,100
we finally go to the point where we have some leftover astral arrays

194
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,433
which we can use to boost some machines

195
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:18,866
like the star core miner

196
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,866
or the daisonsphere ray receiving stations

197
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,233
and on that subject

198
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:26,866
we also figure out a better way of converting all of that sunlight into energy

199
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:30,066
we start by concentrating it all into critical photons

200
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:33,000
then after turning those into antimatter in the Miracle Top

201
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,533
we build a strange matter aggregator

202
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:37,066
where we can pack that antimatter into fuel rods

203
00:09:37,066 --> 00:09:41,033
and this process surely does produce a huge amount of universium byproduct

204
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:44,466
and finally we burn the antimatter in an artificial star

205
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,500
doing so can yield an amount of power

206
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:50,133
that can go even higher than integer 64 energy units per tick

207
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,633
going back to our base

208
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,733
we built a prototype for a better DTPF

209
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:58,300
and the main gimmick this one has is that it can host some modules to boost its working properties

210
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:01,533
but even though we don't have the Perfect Singularity overclock module

211
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:05,866
we can't run it long enough to even consider reaching its 75 percent fuel discount

212
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,666
next we built the Nano Core

213
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:09,300
which with its perfect overclock

214
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,733
will save us from having to automate the Nano forge tier 4

215
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:14,933
but the real game changer was the indestinct tentacle

216
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:18,133
which can do any amount of assembly recipes in a fixed amount of time

217
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:22,500
and with this, we quickly crafted 100 astral arrays in a single crafting job

218
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:24,733
and even though making astral arrays was that easy

219
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:27,466
we realized we can use more unconventional ways

220
00:10:27,566 --> 00:10:30,466
for starters, with the crazy amount of energy at our disposal

221
00:10:30,466 --> 00:10:33,666
we can afford overclocking a 200 astral array eye of harmony

222
00:10:33,866 --> 00:10:36,266
but since making universium like that is still too normal

223
00:10:36,266 --> 00:10:37,900
we upgraded our matter aggregator

224
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,533
so that it will make a bit more universium as by product

225
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,733
and while both running and crafting that machine is relatively cheap

226
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,233
building and chunk loading it was the real hassle

227
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:51,100
and with that, we can finally start crafting our first Stargate all in one craft

228
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,233
we then proceeded into liquefying it

229
00:10:53,266 --> 00:10:56,400
and not worry about the time and energy requirements of such operations

230
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,533
all of our machines are perfectly overclocking

231
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,666
and are powered by the legendary wireless hatch

232
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:03,066
which will make anything craftable in one tick

233
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:06,200
and just like that we obtain the last item of this pack

234
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,266
the twist token

235
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,333
and I guess that was it

236
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:10,866
see you next time

237
00:11:10,866 --> 00:11:11,333
bye bye

238
00:00:00,466 --> 00:00:01,700
欢迎大家回来

239
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:05,400
今天我们要玩GTNH插件扭曲空间

240
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:09,066
这个快速视频将主要关注（？）（确切的？）mod的细节

241
00:00:09,266 --> 00:00:10,400
不用多说

242
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,533
我们的第一个亮点是多块蒸汽锻造锤的替代版本

243
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,300
但即使在我们调查之前

244
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,666
聚光灯很快被大型蒸汽合金冶炼厂抢走

245
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:22,700
这台昂贵的机器最多可以做48次平行

246
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:26,333
需要1安培的高压电源才能不使我们所有的（青铜？）

247
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:30,466
所有的电力都是由我们新的多块太阳能锅炉产生的

248
00:00:30,466 --> 00:00:32,333
我们稍后会更好地看到。

249
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:37,833
继续，我们可以使用一些昂贵但高效的基本蒸汽发生器来为我们的EBF提供动力

250
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:40,933
虽然这种新型发电机可以达到单位能效

251
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:43,700
当负载被移除时，它不会自行关闭

252
00:00:43,866 --> 00:00:46,100
并且也只能产生LV功率

253
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:50,400
所以在MV中，我们必须回到蒸汽涡轮机来过压我们的EBF

254
00:00:50,566 --> 00:00:53,700
接下来，在我们集中电源并进行了一次EBF升级之后

255
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:57,866
我们设置了一些自动化来为下一个亮点制作足够的电路

256
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,600
木眼

257
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:03,666
这台机器将产生许多随机资源以换取大量熔岩

258
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:07,066
然而，由于寻找熔岩的选择是多么有限

259
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:10,000
甚至机器本身也在怀疑这笔交易是否值得

260
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,533
移动到更有问题的机器

261
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:15,200
我将向您展示巨型砖高炉

262
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:19,633
这台机器需要你以任何你能给它的速度给它燃煤来生产钢铁

263
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:23,100
直到它决定名副其实并打破自己

264
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,433
回到实际进度

265
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:26,233
我们不再使用太阳能锅炉

266
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:29,033
到一些高效的天然气发生器

267
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:32,266
这些将保持我们新的小型AE2系统

268
00:01:32,266 --> 00:01:34,800
当我们进入个人层面时

269
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,333
在这里我们将见到两个我们很久以前失去的老朋友

270
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:41,000
加工厂和加工阵列

271
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,600
多亏了扭曲的空间

272
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,500
我们还可以使用双输入总线来简化自动化

273
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:48,633
接下来，我们开始构建通常的基础设施

274
00:01:48,633 --> 00:01:51,400
此时将由闪电尖顶供电

275
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,733
不像避雷针

276
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:55,933
这个更大的版本不需要雷暴来产生能量

277
00:01:56,233 --> 00:01:58,866
然而，它需要一点点的cruotheum来冷却

278
00:01:58,866 --> 00:02:01,033
还有一些铁用于定期维修

279
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,233
接下来我们做了一个大型蒸馏塔

280
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:07,666
我们按需提供从平台到石油加工的各种蒸馏

281
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,700
这也变得更容易由于先进的巨型石油饼干

282
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:14,000
这消除了对输入放置的严格要求

283
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:17,066
然后我们建造了一个最大尺寸的高级洁净室

284
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,466
如果你认为这足够让你发疯

285
00:02:20,466 --> 00:02:23,333
嗯，你还没有考虑到这些过滤器的成本。

286
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,900
不像普通的无尘室

287
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:28,400
这个没有维护也没有能源成本

288
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:32,333
接下来跟上我们的一切主网按需运行

289
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,833
我们建造了一个巨型化学反应堆

290
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:36,466
在我们完成第一个核聚变反应堆之前

291
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,433
一旦我们达到核聚变

292
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,266
我们建了一条先进的电路装配线

293
00:02:40,266 --> 00:02:42,133
没有输入订单要求

294
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,866
并且可以容纳多个印记

295
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,000
如果你认为这是压倒一切

296
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
下一台机器令人兴奋

297
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:51,100
我将向您展示下一个界面

298
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,933
只需查看输出和NEI制作配方

299
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,700
继续，我们做了一点魔法。

300
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:59,100
只够买一个激光计矿工

301
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:03,733
这个多块将快速挖掘米一排一次与奖金财富三

302
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,833
接下来提高我们的魔法自动化速度

303
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,800
我们建立了一个工业魔法矩阵

304
00:03:08,866 --> 00:03:13,066
它可以利用光环节点和激光层能量来加速魔法注入

305
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,433
多亏了这台机器

306
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:17,066
我们现在可以每秒进行几十次输注

307
00:03:17,266 --> 00:03:21,100
我们还将通量生产的风险与停电的风险进行了交易

308
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:24,266
如果那台机器要让你尖叫

309
00:03:24,266 --> 00:03:26,066
我们把它留给下一台机器

310
00:03:26,066 --> 00:03:28,066
字面意思是血腥地狱

311
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:30,633
就像名字和血迹所暗示的那样

312
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:33,533
这台机器将处理血魔祭坛食谱

313
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,700
与之前的不同

314
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,866
它甚至不需要能量来工作

315
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:42,600
虽然我认为这两个可能是我在改装版Minecraft中见过的最好看的多块

316
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,700
这些并不是扭曲空间添加的唯一好看的多块

317
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:49,133
我们还有生态圈增长模拟器

318
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:52,033
每秒能够制作数十万个日志

319
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:54,266
同时使用单安培的紫外线能量

320
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,666
紧挨着它的是大型工业烹饪工厂

321
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:00,600
可以做最大平行度的焦炉食谱

322
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:04,166
但这不是唯一能够并行执行整数32的机器

323
00:04:04,166 --> 00:04:05,833
我们还有一个筛子

324
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:06,266
搅拌机

325
00:04:06,266 --> 00:04:07,200
流体加热器

326
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,166
和一个流体提取器

327
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:11,033
它兼作流体凝固器，能够做到这一点

328
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:14,233
如果您认为整数32并行过于强大

329
00:04:14,233 --> 00:04:17,300
好吧，我们也有能够完美超频的机器

330
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,433
就像电解槽一样

331
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,300
它也兼作离心机

332
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:23,433
最后，结束这一系列压倒性的多块

333
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:27,833
我们还有一台机器，它只需要1/10的能源就可以做出化学反应配方。

334
00:04:28,066 --> 00:04:28,833
最重要的是

335
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:33,600
它也有一些自定义配方，允许您跳过大多数化学生产线处理步骤

336
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,933
移动到一些更复杂的多块

337
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:40,433
我们有这个（有价值的？）锻造，它使用火药来增加其热容

338
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:42,600
在这样做的同时，它还获得了一些能源折扣

339
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,300
制造中子超级便宜

340
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:46,533
当然还有冷却所有这些热锭

341
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:48,500
我们还有热吞噬机

342
00:04:48,866 --> 00:04:50,400
我们还有一个激光驱动的激光器

343
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,733
有一天会实现完美的超频

344
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,533
和4合1金属加工机

345
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,733
在某个时候会接受激光能量

346
00:04:57,033 --> 00:05:00,100
当然，4合1意味着我们必须建造其中的4个。

347
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:04,700
我们还有一个线材轧机，它的平行计数会变长。

348
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:09,100
我们建造的最后一个UV多块是（？）和真空炉

349
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:12,833
这个也会通过变得更高来增加它的平行度

350
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:15,466
接下来我们做了一些微生物桶

351
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,733
那些可以制造一些相当大的批次

352
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:22,833
这需要对输出舱口中的流体量进行一些微调以达到最佳效率

353
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:26,933
有了这些，我们现在买得起超级切割机和超级偏振片。

354
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:28,333
以较小的形式

355
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:32,600
是的，这两个可以增加尺寸以实现更高的并行器速度

356
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:35,233
接下来在建造一条大型装配线之后

357
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,000
不需要输入分离

358
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,700
并且可以做128并行

359
00:05:38,866 --> 00:05:40,233
我们回到我们的激光

360
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:42,333
可以制造有史以来最便宜的DTPF燃料

361
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,933
通过叠加每次套管升级的速度加成

362
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:49,266
DTPF通常存在的另一个问题是原始Infinity Catalyst

363
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:52,866
像往常一样，扭曲提供了一个新的多块来帮助解决这个问题

364
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,866
一般矿石加工TST

365
00:05:54,866 --> 00:05:57,866
将纯矿石的产量乘以4

366
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:01,500
它还提供了大量来自宝石矿石的宝石

367
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,733
除此之外，它还可以做无限的平行

368
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:07,066
跟上我们新的starcore矿工

369
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:09,633
能够产生大量的矿物质

370
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,833
跟上新的电力需求

371
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:14,066
我们开始研究一个真正的戴森球体

372
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:18,333
为此，我们使用戴森发射器结构将太阳帆送入太空

373
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,633
一旦我们有一些围绕我们的恒星运行

374
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:24,200
我们可以开始通过我们的Dyson（地球网络？）天线收集能量

375
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,533
就在那时我们意识到

376
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:29,466
这不会产生任何有意义的能量

377
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:34,033
我们可以通过在更好的恒星周围建造戴森球体来提高产量

378
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:36,400
但产量只会增加10倍

379
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,033
这仍然比对我们有意义的要少几千倍

380
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:46,133
与此同时，制造足够的太阳能帆和适当的模块管理目前可能很昂贵

381
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:49,233
所以与其将这些太阳光线转化为能量

382
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,733
我们开始把它们变成临界光子。

383
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,266
你可以用它来制作一堆机器

384
00:06:54,266 --> 00:06:56,466
或者为了更好的能源反物质

385
00:06:57,666 --> 00:07:00,533
在我们尝试收集能量的新方法失败后

386
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,733
我们回到了我们信任的naquadah燃料

387
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:08,733
在这里，我们可以使用激光智能节点轻松合并发电机的所有激光发电机

388
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:12,933
接下来我们使用超级便宜的电池配方来清楚地制作我们的峡谷

389
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,400
目前这没什么用

390
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,600
因为这座巨型火山的能源效率要高出1000倍

391
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:22,833
熵毁灭者可以毫无问题地冷却无穷无尽的热锭

392
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:28,233
gorge的另一个用途暂时无法炫耀是它的等离子制造能力

393
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:32,400
这次我们可以迅速结束我们聚变隧道的成长

394
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,066
第三层球状闪电

395
00:07:34,066 --> 00:07:37,000
能够以超级便宜的价格制造疯狂数量的血浆

396
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:39,800
这与其他扭曲多块相结合

397
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,333
将使生产DTPF燃料基本免费

398
00:07:42,866 --> 00:07:44,500
把这些东西都好好利用起来

399
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,133
我们需要在生产线上创造奇迹

400
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:51,800
奇迹上衣将完美超频任何电路或电路部件的制作

401
00:07:51,866 --> 00:07:56,500
压倒性的，即使是一台唯一目的是防止电路转换出现电源故障的机器

402
00:07:57,066 --> 00:08:00,600
不管怎样，有了这个，我们现在可以开始我们的和谐之眼进程了。

403
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,500
多亏了三台新机器，我们可以加快速度

404
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,900
第一个是星体计算阵列

405
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,833
这将大大加快我们的搜索速度

406
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,033
由于其巨大的液体冷却器架

407
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:12,833
接下来我们有扭曲的大型反汇编器

408
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:16,400
它可以拆解任何在装配工或装配线上制造的东西

409
00:08:16,433 --> 00:08:21,200
帮助我们找回和谐之眼外壳中包含的一些有价值的材料

410
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,200
最终为这一切提供动力

411
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,866
我们开始围绕一颗更大的恒星建造戴森球体

412
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:28,633
无休止地在它周围拍摄越来越多的镜子

413
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:32,100
这个戴森球体设置没有维护成本

414
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,233
但通过发送更多镜子

415
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:35,700
我们可以超线性地增加我们的能源生产

416
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:39,800
然而，我们每个接收站可以收集多少能量是有限制的

417
00:08:39,866 --> 00:08:41,633
所以我们不得不再建几个。

418
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:44,300
这将给我们和谐之眼一个巨大的推动力

419
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:47,500
但它仍然会给我们留下足够的时间来开发新的多块

420
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,666
比如物质操纵者创世纪

421
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:52,066
可以产生浓缩的UU物质

422
00:08:52,066 --> 00:08:54,133
或者大量正常的UU物质

423
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:55,900
接下来我们有奇迹门

424
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,733
这将使合金爆炸熔炼配方与无限平行的锭

425
00:08:59,866 --> 00:09:02,066
然后我们做了一个微型时空制造者

426
00:09:02,066 --> 00:09:04,900
它制造了几个新零件和更便宜的特斯拉

427
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,700
最后我们有了超级净水器

428
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,833
这将使我们的供水线变得多余

429
00:09:10,266 --> 00:09:12,333
经过几次升级和一些等待时间

430
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:15,100
我们终于到了有一些剩余星体阵列的地步

431
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,433
我们可以用它来提升一些机器

432
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:18,866
就像明星核心矿工一样

433
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,866
或者戴森球体射线接收站

434
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,233
在这个问题上

435
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:26,866
我们也找到了一个更好的方法将所有的太阳光转化为能量

436
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:30,066
我们首先将其全部集中到临界光子中

437
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:33,000
然后在奇迹之巅把它们变成反物质后

438
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,533
我们建立了一个奇怪的物质聚合器

439
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:37,066
我们可以把反物质装进燃料棒

440
00:09:37,066 --> 00:09:41,033
这个过程肯定会产生大量的大学副产品

441
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:44,466
最后我们在人造恒星中燃烧反物质

442
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,500
这样做可以产生大量的能量

443
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:50,133
甚至可以超过整数每滴答64个能量单位

444
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,633
回到我们的基地

445
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,733
我们为更好的DTPF构建了一个原型

446
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:58,300
这个的主要噱头是它可以托管一些模块来提高它的工作性能

447
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:01,533
但即使我们没有完美奇点超频模块

448
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:05,866
我们甚至不能考虑达到75%的燃料折扣。

449
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,666
接下来我们建造了纳米核心

450
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:09,300
凭借其完美的超频

451
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,733
将使我们不必自动化纳米锻造层4

452
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:14,933
但真正改变游戏规则的是不确定的触手

453
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:18,133
可以在固定时间内完成任意数量的组装配方

454
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:22,500
有了这个，我们在一次制作工作中快速制作了100个星体阵列

455
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:24,733
尽管制作星体阵列很容易

456
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:27,466
我们意识到我们可以用更多非常规的方式

457
00:10:27,566 --> 00:10:30,466
首先，我们拥有大量的能量

458
00:10:30,466 --> 00:10:33,666
我们可以超频200星体阵列和谐之眼

459
00:10:33,866 --> 00:10:36,266
但是既然这样的大学还是太正常了

460
00:10:36,266 --> 00:10:37,900
我们升级了物质聚合器

461
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,533
这样它就会像产品一样更具普遍性。

462
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,733
虽然运行和制造这台机器都相对便宜

463
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,233
建造和大块装载是真正的麻烦

464
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:51,100
有了这个我们终于可以在一艘飞船上打造我们的第一个星际之门了

465
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,233
然后我们开始液化它

466
00:10:53,266 --> 00:10:56,400
而不用担心这种操作的时间和精力需求

467
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,533
我们所有的机器都完美超频

468
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,666
并由传奇的无线舱门供电

469
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:03,066
这将使任何东西在一个滴答声中变得可制作

470
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:06,200
就这样，我们得到了这个包的最后一件东西。

471
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,266
扭曲的象征

472
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,333
我想这就是原因

473
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:10,866
下次见

474
00:11:10,866 --> 00:11:11,333
拜拜

